TYPE ERROR: Effect laundering in impl of 'speak' for interface 'Speak': the body performs <Stdout>, which is not sourced from any argument and is not declared by the method's effect row, so it is absorbed into a declared effect variable a caller can instantiate to <> — a function typed pure would then silently perform it. Either declare the effect in the method's return row (e.g. `<Stdout | e>`), or make it flow from an argument (perform it only through a callback carrying `<e>`).
